Cell["\<\
A simple encoding: transforming categorical variables into discrete numbers, \
for example \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]female\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]->0 and \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]male\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]->1, or education level (\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]PhD\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Master\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]higher\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]secondary\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]primary\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]no education\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote])->(5,4,3,2,1,0).  \
\>", "Subitem",
